name: assimilatory sulfite reductase (NADPH)
names: sulfite (reduced nicotinamide adenine dinucleotide phosphate) reductase
classes: Acting on a sulfur group of donors;
With NAD+ or NADP+ as acceptor
reaction: hydrogen sulfide + 3 NADP+ + 3 H2O = sulfite + 3 NADPH + 3 H+ [RN:R00858]
comment: Contains siroheme, [4Fe-4S] cluster, FAD and FMN. The enzyme, which catalyses the six-electron reduction of sulfite to sulfide, is involved in sulfate assimilation in bacteria and yeast. Different from EC 1.8.99.5, dissimilatory sulfite reductase, which is involved in prokaryotic sulfur-based energy metabolism. cf. EC 1.8.7.1, assimilatory sulfite reductase (ferredoxin).
